    "The inorganic and organic P pools are accessible by plants via alternative acquisition and mobilization strategies (Lambers, 2022).",
    "P linked to primary minerals is the form that is present in the parent lithology.",
    "This form of soil P is commonly named primary mineral P and is transformed by weathering, which liberates inorganic P in the soil.",
    "Here we assume that the primary mineral P is composed of the fraction extracted with HCl (hydrochloric acidcalcium-bound P) in the sequential fractionation process.",
    "The mean residence time of primary mineral P falls into timescales that vary from years to millennia (Helfenstein et al., 2020)."
